      "text": "It's fine to target compatibility.  Should be a two-way street.\n\nSecureStrings and Mutexes aren't \"rough edges\" on Linux:  They're differences between operating systems.\n\nYesterday brought a decent thread about why SecureString is not actually secure.  \n\nIIRC Mutexes are similar fictions."
